The paper focuses on a framework for efficient multi-contact optimal control, which is a topic related to robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions the use of differential geometry, which is a topic related to systems and control theory, and optimization methods, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper showcases the performance of the framework using different tasks, which may involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible category as well.
